    "description": [
        {
            "text": "\"Quality Factor\", of a resonant circuit, is a measure of the \"goodness\" or quality of a resonant circuit. A higher value for this figure of merit correspondes to a more narrow bandwith, which is desirable in many applications. More formally, $Q$ is the ratio of power stored to power dissipated in the circuit reactance and resistance, respectively",
            "lang": "en"
        }
